abstract: Mr. Skelos and his son, Adam, had been retried after their earlier convictions for corruption were overturned on appeal.
snippet: Mr. Skelos and his son, Adam, had been retried after their earlier convictions for corruption were overturned on appeal.
lead_paragraph: Dean G. Skelos, the former New York State Senate majority leader who wielded sweeping power in the Legislature for nearly a decade, was sentenced to four years and three months in prison on Wednesday for a corruption scheme involving his son.

abstract: These writers are embracing a more elastic literary form — the novel — and a number of recent works, often genre-bending as well as gender-bending, have won critical acclaim.

lead_paragraph: NORTHAMPTON, Mass. — The Pioneer Valley in western Massachusetts is a cradle of social progress — a place where L.G.B.T.Q. is often followed by I.A. (for intersex and asexual), there’s a Stonewall Center (now 33 years old), and gender-nonconforming parents have a nickname of choice (it’s “Baba”).

headline_main: New York Today: An Uncomfortable Debate

abstract: What you need to know from the first and only debate between Governor Andrew Cuomo and his Republican opponent, Marcus Molinaro.
snippet: What you need to know from the first and only debate between Governor Andrew Cuomo and his Republican opponent, Marcus Molinaro.
lead_paragraph: It finally happened: After days of back-and-forth over who was too afraid to face whom, Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo and his Republican challenger, Marcus J. Molinaro, squared off on Tuesday in their first and likely only debate.

abstract: Some pioneering programs are teaching boys to question gender roles, both for their own well-being and as a way to prevent sexual violence.
snippet: Some pioneering programs are teaching boys to question gender roles, both for their own well-being and as a way to prevent sexual violence.
lead_paragraph: “In here, we get to say stuff we wouldn’t normally say in front of other people. And we don’t judge each other,” said a seventh grader with dark curls. “Boys should have a safe space to talk about things that matter to us,” said another seventh grader with a hint of a Canadian accent.

abstract: A three-run home run by Eduardo Nunez was enough offense for Chris Sale and the Red Sox in an 8-4 victory.
snippet: A three-run home run by Eduardo Nunez was enough offense for Chris Sale and the Red Sox in an 8-4 victory.
lead_paragraph: It was not the pitchers’ duel that many had hoped for, but Chris Sale and a group of Boston relievers managed to get past Clayton Kershaw and the Dodgers bullpen on Tuesday as Boston beat Los Angeles, 8-4, in Game 1 of the 2018 World Series.

abstract: The first and only debate between Gov. Andrew Cuomo and his Republican foe, Marcus Molinaro, devolved into a shouting match over the other’s record.
snippet: The first and only debate between Gov. Andrew Cuomo and his Republican foe, Marcus Molinaro, devolved into a shouting match over the other’s record.
lead_paragraph: It started with a coin toss and ended with a song request. But in the hour between, the first and only debate between Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo and his Republican opponent, Marcus J. Molinaro, devolved into a shouting match in which discussions about New York’s challenges were largely eclipsed by name-calling and aspersions about the other’s record.

abstract: The president’s unsubstantiated charge that “unknown Middle Easterners” were part of the migrant caravan was an escalation of his efforts to stoke fears ahead of the Nov. 6 vote.
snippet: The president’s unsubstantiated charge that “unknown Middle Easterners” were part of the migrant caravan was an escalation of his efforts to stoke fears ahead of the Nov. 6 vote.
lead_paragraph: President Trump on Monday sharply intensified a Republican campaign to frame the midterm elections as a battle over immigration and race, issuing a dark and factually baseless warning that “unknown Middle Easterners” were marching toward the American border with Mexico.
